Here are the most helpful links for understanding our listing process today:

1/ http://tinyurl.com/cb-listings-guide
2/ https://www.coinbase.com/blog/a-guide-to-listing-assets-on-coinbase
3/ https://help.coinbase.com/en/coinbase/other-topics/other/asset-issuer-faq

Information on the framework we use for individual assets is below:

1/ Security [chains]: https://help.coinbase.com/en/coinbase/privacy-and-security/other/asset-security-review
2/ Security [tokens]: https://www.coinbase.com/blog/how-coinbase-reviews-tokens-on-ethereum-for-technical-security-risks

(Continued)

Asset review process for Legal and Compliance:

1/ Legal: https://help.coinbase.com/en/coinbase/privacy-and-security/other/asset-legal-review
2/ Compliance: https://help.coinbase.com/en/coinbase/other-topics/legal-policies/enhancing-trust-with-regulatory-compliance

Technical considerations:

Rosetta API integration (for chains only): https://www.rosetta-api.org/

(Native blockchain assets take much longer to integrate than token standards. Rosetta implementation is required)

We've made efforts to bring transparency to the listings process through these guides - hopefully this helps explain different pillars of the process: https://warpcast.com/zosegal/0x6014c78c

We also have a dedicated Listings Partner Success team ready to answer questions if you're working on a project.

With that said, if you've come across any other exchanges/platforms with more thorough documentation than this, I'd love to know so we can take a look. 

Always looking to increase transparency and help developers navigate this, and welcome any feedback.
